CLASS:: RedDefault
SUMMARY:: a hacked default synth
CATEGORIES:: Red

DESCRIPTION::
The point of this class is that any event you try to play with the default synth will sound a lot better ;-) e.g. try the code in link::Tutorials/Streams-Patterns-Events5:: or link::Tutorials/Streams-Patterns-Events6:: before and after installing.

NOTE::
This class will overwrite your default synth at recompile. Though it is easy to undo and get back to normal.
::

definitionList::
## install ||
list::
## if you haven't already, install redDefault as normal via code::Quarks.gui::. Or run the following... code::Quarks.install("redDefault")::
## recompile supercollider and redDefault will overwrite the default synthdef.
::
## uninstall ||
list::
## manually delete the file default.scsyndef in your synthdefs directory. Or run the following... code::("rm"+(SynthDef.synthDefDir++"default.scsyndef").quote).unixCmd::
## uninstall redDefault via the quarks gui. Or run the followingâ€¦ code::Quarks.uninstall("redDefault")::
## last recompile supercollider and a brand new default.scsynth will be created for you.
::
